daily_routine: Chen would wake at 4 AM to listen to the river's voice - the subtle
  sounds of fish movements, water currents, and seasonal changes her grandmother taught
  her to interpret. She'd cast her nets based on these acoustic cues, just as her
  family had for eight generations. Afternoons were spent mending nets while reciting
  the old river songs that encoded fishing wisdom.
